<reference id="area" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>area</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>area</xmlelement> element describes a linkable area within an
<xmlelement>imagemap</xmlelement>. It allows the author to specify a shape within the image, the
coordinates of that shape, and a link target for the area.</shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>utilities domain<indexterm><xmlelement>area</xmlelement></indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section id="specialization-hierachy">
            <title>Specialization hierarchy</title>
            <p>The <xmlelement>area</xmlelement> element is specialized from
                    <xmlelement>div</xmlelement>. It is defined in the utilities-domain module.</p>
        </section>
